<LegalLayout
  title="Cookie Policy — Routinly"
  description="How Routinly uses cookies and similar technologies on routinly.org and app.routinly.org, and how to manage your preferences."
  heading="Cookie Policy"
  lastUpdated="July 1, 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains how Routinly uses cookies and similar technologies on
    routinly.org and app.routinly.org.
  </p>

  <h2>1. What cookies are</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help the
    site remember your session, preferences, and activity. Similar technologies include local
    storage and pixels; we refer to all of these as "cookies".
  </p>

  <h2>2. Cookies we use</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Strictly necessary.</strong> Authentication, session management, and security cookies
    required for the Service to work. These cannot be disabled.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Preferences.</strong> Remember settings like language and interface choices.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>Analytics.</strong> Help us understand how the Service is used so we can improve it.
    Analytics cookies are set only with your consent, and data is aggregated wherever possible.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Third-party cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Some cookies are set by service providers acting on our behalf, such as our payment processor
    during checkout. These providers are bound by data processing agreements and may not use your
    data for their own purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Managing cookies</h2>
  <p>
    You can accept or decline non-essential cookies via the consent banner on your first visit,
    and change your choice at any time from the cookie settings link in the footer. You can also
    delete or block cookies in your browser settings; note that blocking necessary cookies will
    prevent you from signing in.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Changes and contact</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy as our use of cookies changes. Questions:
    <a href="mailto:privacy@routinly.org">privacy@routinly.org</a>. See also our
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
